{"description":"<div class=\"mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><p>Fun short dry canyon with 4 rappels max ~80'. Scenic hike with Sunrise Arch and others along the approach. Just across the Lower Salt river from water users #1. In winter (~8 cfs) can use a river rock fisherman crossing and keep your feet dry. In summer (~450  cfs) will require some swimming or packraft crossing.\n<\/p>\n<meta property=\"mw:PageProp\/toc\" \/>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Approach\">Approach<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Cross river. Go west, or right up obvious gully. Follow use trail to saddle passing Sunrise Arch and scrambling up a narrow gully. Then travel flat ground to obvious drainage.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Descent\">Descent<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Downclimb or possible 20' rappel off a chockstone. Easy slot with about six foot drop.\n<\/p><p><b>R1<\/b>: 40' off boulder backed up by tree LDC.\n<\/p><p>A few easy downclimbs.\n<\/p><p><b>R2<\/b>: 80' off of boulder RDC. Followed immediately by downclimb.\n<\/p><p><b>R3<\/b>: 60' two-tier drop off of tree and boulder LDC.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Exit\">Exit<\/h2><\/div>\n<p>Stay RDC as canyon ends for least bushy way to river. Follow river west to where crossed on approach.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Red_tape\">Red tape<\/h2><\/div>\n<p><b>Closed for bald eagle nesting from 12\/01-6\/30<\/b> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https:\/\/www.fs.usda.gov\/Internet\/FSE_DOCUMENTS\/fseprd532582.pdf\">https:\/\/www.fs.usda.gov\/Internet\/FSE_DOCUMENTS\/fseprd532582.pdf<\/a>\n<\/p><p>Tonto Pass or National Parks Pass required for parking.\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Beta_sites\">Beta sites<\/h2><\/div>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https:\/\/waterdata.usgs.gov\/az\/nwis\/uv\/?site_no=09502000&amp;PARAmeter_cd=00065,00060\">https:\/\/waterdata.usgs.gov\/az\/nwis\/uv\/?site_no=09502000&amp;PARAmeter_cd=00065,00060<\/a>\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Trip_reports_and_media\">Trip reports and media<\/h2><\/div>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https:\/\/shadowcatadventures.com\/pony-express\/\">https:\/\/shadowcatadventures.com\/pony-express\/<\/a>\n<\/p>\n<div class=\"mw-heading mw-heading2\"><h2 id=\"Background\">Background<\/h2><\/div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw‐api‐ext.codfw.main‐6779cc57fc‐gmtt9\nCached time: 20240914191950\nCache expiry: 2592000\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: [show‐toc]\nCPU time usage: 0.006 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.007 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 21\/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0\/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0\/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2\/100\nExpensive parser function count: 0\/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0\/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0\/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0\/400\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n<\/div>","url":"https:\/\/ropewiki.com\/Pony_Express","months":["Nov","Oct"],"geojson":{"type":"FeatureCollection","features":[{"properties":{"name":"Exit"},"geometry":{"coordinates":[[-111.53549,33.554554,0],[-111.535545,33.55467,0],[-111.53563,33.554813,0],[-111.53567,33.554928,0],[-111.53587,33.555073,0],[-111.53609,33.55517,0],[-111.5364,33.5553,0],[-111.53722,33.555412,0],[-111.53778,33.555492,0],[-111.53828,33.55542,0],[-111.5389,33.555275,0],[-111.53963,33.555035,0],[-111.54094,33.555233,0],[-111.54128,33.555492,0]],"type":"LineString"},"type":"Feature"},{"properties":{"name":"Pony Express"},"geometry":{"coordinates":[[-111.53423,33.551582,0],[-111.533966,33.551723,0],[-111.53399,33.55199,0],[-111.534096,33.552227,0],[-111.53405,33.552383,0],[-111.53405,33.552525,0],[-111.53457,33.552876,0],[-111.5346,33.553253,0],[-111.53486,33.553696,0],[-111.53511,33.553997,0],[-111.5352